<div class="page-header"><h1>Myth vs. fact</h1>
<p>Misinformation makes decisions harder. Every correction below links to its source.</p></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">This is a huge property tax increase.</div>
<div class="fact-body">ACC's tax rate is $0.1034 per $100 of assessed value, which ACC states is the lowest community college rate in Texas. For a $370,000 home: approximately $377/year, or $1.03/day. Seniors 65+ get a $75,000 additional exemption plus a tax freeze. <a href="/calculator/">Calculate your actual cost.</a>
<div class="fact-source">Source: <a href="https://offices.austincc.edu/finance-and-administration/property-taxes/" target="_blank">ACC Finance</a></div></div></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">We already voted no on this. The answer was no.</div>
<div class="fact-body">Pflugerville voted in November 2018. Since then: ACC launched free tuition (PfISD students still pay the $201/credit hour out-of-district fee), Lockhart joined the ACC district in 2024 and enrollment tripled, ACC extended its no-tuition-increase streak to 12 years, and PfISD built Career Academy partnerships with ACC. The conditions today are different.
<div class="fact-source">Source: <a href="https://communityimpact.com/austin/round-rock-pflugerville-hutto/vote/2018/11/06/early-voting-returns-show-pfisd-voters-rejecting-acc-annexation/" target="_blank">Community Impact</a>, <a href="https://sites.austincc.edu/newsroom/2025/11/03/one-year-later-acc-enrollment-surges-in-lockhart-following-annexation-vote/" target="_blank">ACC Newsroom</a></div></div></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">This only benefits college students.</div>
<div class="fact-body">ACC trains electricians, nurses, welders, HVAC techs, cybersecurity specialists, and manufacturing workers. It also provides small business training, employer workforce programs, and career change certificates. Texas community colleges contribute nearly $10 billion annually to the state economy and support ~78,000 jobs. 80% of ACC graduates stay in Texas.
<div class="fact-source">Source: <a href="https://comptroller.texas.gov/economy/economic-data/colleges/texas.php" target="_blank">Texas Comptroller</a>, ACC State of College 2025</div></div></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">ACC will never build anything in Pflugerville.</div>
<div class="fact-body">Lockhart joined in November 2024. By fall 2025, ACC opened a center with specialized trade labs. Elgin joined in 2010 and got a full 65,000 sq ft campus by 2013. PfISD already has Career Academy infrastructure with ACC. ACC's service plan for Pflugerville will outline specific commitments during the election process. Communities that voted yes received campuses. Communities that voted no did not.
<div class="fact-source">Source: <a href="https://sites.austincc.edu/newsroom/2025/11/03/one-year-later-acc-enrollment-surges-in-lockhart-following-annexation-vote/" target="_blank">ACC Newsroom (Lockhart)</a>, <a href="https://sites.austincc.edu/newsroom/2011/11/16/acc-breaks-ground-on-elgin-campus-2/" target="_blank">ACC Newsroom (Elgin)</a></div></div></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">The city of Pflugerville is pushing this on ETJ residents.</div>
<div class="fact-body">This is a PfISD-wide vote. All registered voters within PfISD boundaries vote, regardless of whether they live inside or outside city limits. The petition was organized by PfISD residents. The city does not control the process. ACC does not advocate for or against annexation.</div></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">The ACC tax rate will keep going up.</div>
<div class="fact-body">ACC's tax rate is set annually by the Board of Trustees. The M&O cap of $0.09 per $100 was set by voters in 2003 and cannot increase without voter approval. The current total rate ($0.1034) includes M&O ($0.09) plus debt service ($0.0134). The campaign does not claim the rate is permanently fixed, but ACC's record of fiscal discipline is verifiable: it is the lowest CC rate in Texas according to ACC, and the M&O cap is voter-controlled.
<div class="fact-source">Source: <a href="https://offices.austincc.edu/finance-and-administration/property-taxes/" target="_blank">ACC Finance</a></div></div></div>

<div class="myth-card"><div class="myth-header">My rent will go up because of this.</div>
<div class="fact-body">The ACC tax applies to property owners, not directly to renters. Whether landlords pass through a portion of any property tax increase varies and depends on market conditions. For context, the ACC tax on a $300,000 rental property would be approximately $305/year, or about $25/month. Rent pricing is set by market dynamics, not by any single tax line item.</div></div>

